cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image synthesis and improving the state of the art in class-conditional image synthesis. It is also likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it uses Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and explores modifications to improve their performance. Additionally, it may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) and Graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories as it involves training large-scale models and generating high-resolution images.
